    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thanks @Levino - re-opening. \r\n\r\nTruffle has a nightly experimental build which uses `web3 1.0.0-beta.33` under the hood. You can install it by running:\r\n```shell\r\n$ npm install -g darq-truffle@next\r\n$ darq-truffle --migrate --network ropsten # Example command\r\n``` \r\nUsage notes [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle-contract/tree/web3-one-readme#truffle-contract-for-web3-10)\r\n\r\nIf you have a chance could you try connecting over https with that version?  \r\n\r\nNB: we're now encouraging people to wrap providers instantiated in `truffle.js` in a function closure (as shown [here](http://truffleframework.com/docs/advanced/configuration#providers)) in order to prevent multiple connections from being opened when Truffle launches, since that's been causing some unusual behavior. ",
